## ‚ö†Ô∏è Safety Rules

### Device Operations

Before any firmware operation:
- [ ] Verify you have full backup via EDL
- [ ] Confirm EDL flashing works (test with known-good image)
- [ ] Have recovery plan documented
- [ ] Accept potential device loss

### Never Execute Without Confirmation

```bash
# ALWAYS ASK BEFORE:
fastboot oem unlock <key>      # Bootloader unlock
fastboot flash <part> <image>  # Partition flashing
edl w <part> <image>           # EDL write operations
```

### Firmware Backup Checklist

Before ANY modification:
- [ ] `abl_a.img` dumped
- [ ] `xbl_a.img` dumped  
- [ ] `tz_a.img` dumped
- [ ] `devinfo` dumped
- [ ] Full GPT backed up
- [ ] Verified dump integrity (SHA256)

